                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.6368/147.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Vice Consul <persName type="from">Bevan</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Tampico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-01-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 11, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Penn-Mex Oil Company and the Aguilar Petroleum Company have been closed down by
                    decree signed by Sub-Secretary of Fomento and authorized by First Chief of the
                    Constitutionalist Army.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bevan.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
